Gunmen Kill 16 in Northern Nigeria Villages, Vanguard Says

-- B y   V i n c e n t   N w a n m a
-- 
2011-05-07T09:57:30Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-07/gunmen-kill-16-in-northern-nigeria-villages-vanguard-says.html
     May 7 (Bloomberg)-- Unidentified gunmen killed 16 people
and burnt homes in an attack yesterday on villages in Bauchi
state, northern  Nigeria ,  Vanguard  reported, citing John
Abakasanga, Commissioner of Police in the state.  The attacks came three weeks after many people were killed
in post-election protests in the state and other parts of
northern Nigeria, after President  Goodluck Jonathan , a
southerner, was declared winner, the Lagos-based newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Vincent Nwanma in Lagos at 
 vnwanma@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Antony Sguazzin at 
 asguazzin@bloomberg.net . 